        "class": "bld",
        "text": "4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The previous statement is enforced by denying the opposite of it. The construction, ‘he that saith,’ ‘he that loveth,’ &c. now takes the place of ‘if we say,’ ‘if we walk,’ &c., but without change of meaning; and this continues down to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "1 John 2:11",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 John 2:11",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", after which both constructions cease and a new division begins. Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 1:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which is exactly parallel to this: ‘to know Him’ = ‘to have fellowship with Him,’ and ‘not to keep His commandments’ = ‘to walk in darkness.’",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and keepeth not",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] By the negative which he uses (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") S. John states the case as gently as possible, without asserting that any such person exists (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 2:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
