  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 4.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The participial substantive ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ὁ λέγων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " now takes the place of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐάν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with the subjunctive, but the two are equivalent (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 1:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which is almost exactly parallel to this, and shows what \"knowing him\" really is, viz. having fellowship with him, just as not keeping his commandments is the same as walking in darkness). St. John says, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "μὴ τηρῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "οὐ τηρῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", the case being hypothetical - if there be such a man, he is a liar, and has no idea of truth (see on 1 John 1:8). He must have lost the very power of recognizing truth to maintain that he knows Christ, when he habitually transgresses his commands. It is no great thing, as Bode says, to know as the devils do, who \"believe and tremble.\" 1 John 2:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
